</gmd:citation>          <gmd:abstract>             <gco:CharacterString>The National Highway Planning Network (NTAD 2014) is a comprehensive network database of the nation's major highway system. It consists of the nation's highways comprised of Rural Arterials, Urban Principal Arterials and all National Highway System routes. The data set covers the 48 contiguous States plus the District of Columbia, Alaska, Hawaii, and Puerto Rico. The nominal scale of the data set is 1:100,000 with a maximal positional error of \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd80 meters.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>The primary purpose of this geospatial data set is to serve the FHWA needs in highway planning, policy analysis, visualization of the Highway Performance Monitoring System (HPMS) database and network modeling.
